# =========================================================================
# === A gitignore for a Vite + React + Tailwind + Node.js + Express.js project ===
# =========================================================================

## Dependencies
# This directory contains all project dependencies and should be regenerated
# by running `npm install` or `yarn install`.
/node_modules
# For monorepos, you might have node_modules in sub-packages.
**/node_modules

---

## Build & Production Output
# These directories contain the compiled/bundled code for deployment.
# They are generated by running a build command (e.g., `npm run build`).
/dist
/build
/out
/.output
/.vercel

---

## Caching & Development
# Caches created by tools like Vite to speed up development builds.
/.vite/
/.cache/

# Test coverage reports.
/coverage/

# Log files can contain sensitive information and vary between environments.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# Other generated files from Node.js runtime.
report.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.json
*.pid
*.seed
*.gz

---

## Environment Variables
# Environment variable files contain secrets like API keys and database passwords.
# NEVER commit these files to version control.
# Instead, create a `.env.example` file with placeholder values and commit that file.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.development
.env.production
.env.test

# You might want to commit a template file, so you can explicitly un-ignore it:
# !.env.example

---

## OS & IDE Configuration
# Files generated by operating systems and code editors.

# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# IDEs
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace

---

## Optional: Project-Specific Files
# Add any other files or directories specific to your project that
# should not be tracked by Git.

# Example: Directory for user-uploaded content
# /uploads/